inn1.comm: leg-side wide to start with and that's greeted by cheers from the crowd
tickled behind square and that's Joyce's first World Cup run
on the money to the righthander and that's defended forward with the bat nestling with the pad
driven slowly to mid-on where they decide to "Wait!"
flies that one through the corridor, good line and length, and Vaughan makes the correct decision to let that one pass him by
very wide outside off
low and outside off again
great ball that one, cutting him right up - ball of the over so far
left alone outside off
pitches outside off and that's worked to third man
over the wicket to the righthander and slants that across him on a good length
going across Vaughan and that's left alone outside off with a hint of movement
driven to mid-on
Vaughan sneaks forward and tickles that off his toes to midwicket for some loud cheers from the crowd
wanders down the wicket towards the off-side and drives that one to cover
straight, taken off the toes and that's eased through midwicket
driven to cover off the back foot
left alone outside off, a hint of swing
overstepping and worked to short midwicket
slanted across the lefthander who shoulders arms
overstepping again - Cummins trying to find his rhythm here - and Joyce flashes a cover drive but doesn't connect
driven slowly to cover and they decide not to run
sloppy from the keeper, the ball just not carrying through, and he tries to get his body behind the ball but fails
quick run from Vaughan as that's worked off the back foot to the leg side
lefthander to lefthander again and that one swings away from him a touch on its way through to the keeper
tickled into the covers
a hint of swing again and Joyce can only bring his bat down on that one as he works it to the covers
Joyce thinks about having a dart at that one, presenting his bat just behind the pad
timed away just inside the cover boundary
and he cuts this back into Joyce who gets a big, fat inside edge
well bowled, trying to angle this across Joyce who dabs down on it
defended back to the bowler
wide of the off stump and rightly called so
better line this time and defended on the front foot, cautiously and watchfully by Joyce

very wide and Joyce somehow manages to reach it, without really moving his feet, flaying it Trescothick-stylee through cover. Good effort from the fielder but he dragged the ball over the line and so, twas four
ah, better from Joyce, moving his feet this time and spanking it through the same cover region. No chance of stopping that
pushed to leg but Vaughan can't time it and it's dibbled to leg
ooh outside edge there, Vaughan prodding at it and it falls just short of first slip...who is somehow nutmegged
delightful. On leg, Vaughan simply turns his wrists and clips it through midwicket
driven to mid-off
pure quality. Bagai swinging this into Vaughan, but it's too full and he simply drives through the line and sends it firmly back past the bowler for four
better length, defended to cover
swings away down leg
defended forward
comes forward to try to ease that to cover but doesn't get hold of it
timed away through cover, a push of a drive with no follow-through and that's fluffed on the boundary. Cummins unimpressed, hands on hips, as well he might be
straight, the batsman comes forward again but jams his bat down on the ball in the end
dinked off the face of the bat through the gap at cover and Codrington sets off in hot pursuit
shoulders arms and leaves that easily outside off
across the righthander and driven easily to mid-on for a safe single
outside off, full, and driven into the ground to cover
right up there, just outside off, and that's defended down again
outside off again, Joyce plays that one off the back foot to the man short in at cover
similar ball, similar result, Joyce just pressing his bat down on that one
a hint of away swing again and Joyce is content to leave that one alone as it goes on gently to the keeper
on a good length and that's nibbled out to cover, the batsmen looking for the single, but deciding not to take it
worked down off the back foot into the covers again
attempted yorker and there's a half-hearted appeal to one which took an inside edge on to the pad
drags that down short and wide and Vaughan times that nicely off the back foot with a crashing cut through point to bring up the fifty
easily worked off the back foot to square - Vaughan thought about the second but Joyce wasn't so keen
overstepping and that's symptomatic of Cummins' lack of rhythm out here - he's been spraying the ball around in search of his groove
down leg this time and that's the 14th extra already, Joyce chasing it round
driven straight to cover, trying to pierce the field, but finding the fielder instead
places that on a good length and that's defended down
across the righthander again, a good length, and again that's worked down
defended again
defended forward on the front foot
the ball pops down to point
worked off the toes through midwicket
worked off the front foot, slowly, to midwicket
drags down and that's just timed away beautifully through the on-side by Vaughan, who just waited for it
played off the back foot to point
worked into short midwicket
pushed up there and that's tickled into short midwicket
hit slightly harder to midwicket
defended this time
driven through covers
comes forward to defend
on the money and pressed down without any power into the covers
eased into the covers for a scrambled single
slower ball worked off the toes powerfully, but straight to the fielder at square leg
driven to mid-off
waits for that one and dibs down on it
comes forward and leans over in defence
worked into the covers
round the wicket, by the way, and that's defended on the front foot, Joyce being kept in check
defended forward into the covers
nicely timed off the back foot to mid-off and there's a good quick single that's been taken there
worked into the covers off the back foot
wide outside off and that's worked out inside the cover boundary
on leg and that's worked off the toes into short midwicket
just short of a six, there, with that one-bounce four which was lofted over midwicket
great shot from Vaughan, straight driven back past the bowler and that one fair races away it does
swept off the front foot, not quite in the middle of the bat, and there's a single to midwicket
swept off the front foot behind square
Vaughan moves down the pitch to try to give himself room to bunt that over the top, a bit of a headrush, there
defended forward
another dot again for Joyce against Davison
worked behind square
quick through the air, on Joyce's leg who whips it for a cheeky Irish single
too short, whipped straight to midwicket
pushed to cover but again he can't find the gap
driven more expansively this time, squarer. but can't evade the fielder
pushed to the bowler's left who does well, diving to stop
clipped to mid-on and at last Vaughan takes a single
lovely placement from Vaughan, just working it wide of midwicket
delightfully cover-driven but it's well stopped
drifting down leg
the wrong line, on middle stump and turning further down leg
and again. This is poor stuff from Davison. Enough turn, but the wrong line
that's better. Outside off, turning back in and cramping Vaughan for room who plays it off the back foot
too short, pumped through midwicket without much power and, frankly, that is a shocking piece of fielding. Very village there, somehow diving over the top of it
dropped a typically lazy shot from Joyce into the covers but it's shelled by the man there, Chumney, the 38-year-old
pushed to leg
cut back of point
takes a step outside leg, trying to smite it but he gets a thick inside edge here
a crunching cut but he finds point
oh dear. That's ugly from Joyce, sweeping a ball far too short to be sweeping. A mis-sweep, if you like
defended on the back foot
pushed out to cover
cor, that's a beauty. A skip down the pitch and Joyce hammered it straight over his head for a powerful six
oh, well played, just driving this inside out through extra cover
defended on the front foot
touch too short and Vaughan calmly pushes it off the back foot through midwicket
too short and wide, Vaughan cuts it - without really hammering it, just timing it and placing it superbly through the packed infield
and this time he stands tall, punching it to mid-off
very neatly played, Vaughan check-driving it through cover
"no" he roars after nudging this one to leg
crash: expansively driven but straight to extra cover
and there you go. Once again Vaughan falls when he's well placed. Cleverly bowled, holding it back a touch and he slaps it straight to backward point
clipped, without timing, to long-on for a single
easily flicked through midwicket
skips down the pitch but decides against driving over the top, instead poking it into the man at cover who dives, makes a good stop but sends in a poor throw
neatly, calmly turned to midwicket by Bell
full and straight, pushed to mid-off
and it's defended on the front foot to end the over
poor start, drifting down leg and it's worked through midwicket
Calmly defended on the front foot by Bell
again a good line on off stump, just short of a length and Bell is observant and watchful in defence
a touch quicker? Perhaps. Bell prods at it back to the bowler
blocked out once more
very good line, on middle and turning away. Bell gives it due respect
full toss, pumped down the ground
tossed up high and pushed back to the bowler
turned around the corner
reasonable line and length, good enough to prevent Joyce doing anything with it
worked to leg, but no run on offer there
Joyce comes forward and is rapped high on his front pad
worked to mid-off
half a skip down the pitch before punching it to long-on
worked to short midwicket
half a stifled appeal as Joyce is rapped on the pads, but he's well outside the line
firmly clonked to long-on who's just been moved out from mid-on. Good batting
very neatly slept, ah that's class but the fielder does well to haul it back in and prevent four
attempts to late-cut this but misses out
just clipped, without power, but tidily through midwicket
dropped very well bowled, tempting Joyce into an expansive drive. A thick inside edge hammered into the wicketkeeper's knee. Not the easiest of catches, but they should be taken
driven out to long-off
noodled to leg
deliciously hit through the covers, but again without sufficient power to take it for four
ooh, Bell played this very late, off the back foot, cutting late
fuller this time and it's defended
fuller still, right up in the blockhole, and it's firmly blocked out
Poor line on leg stump, pushed through midwicket this time
and there's his fifty, clipping this to a deep midwicket
punched to mid-off
Bell dances down the pitch (salsa) but can only drive it back to the bowler
clipped off the back foot, fluently, through midwicket for two
wide of the off stump and too short, allowing Bell to rock back and ping it off the back foot
ooh, well bowled - Joyce drives, looking to send it over the top but gets a thick outside edge. A bit of fortune there
off the back foot and wristily forced to leg
a skip down the pitch, the bowler adjusts his length and Bell is then forced into defence
defended on the front foot
swept hard around the corner
tip-and-run to cover
flicked aerially over midwicket, very well placed
sponged to long-off
defended on the front foot
ah, delightful short, handsomely lofted over the infield and wide of long-off. Powerfully, commandingly struck
worked to leg
effortlessly punched off the back foot, guiding it through cover, albeit without much power
well bowled! Flatter and quicker and Bell was beaten, trying to work it to leg but it rushed onto him. Lucky not to get an edge to the keeper
too short, nudged to leg
worked to leg
an iron-wristed reverse-sweep
much better. Swept hard into the deep for a single
pushed through midwicket. Too full
nearly! Quicker ball hurrying Joyce who is rushed into defence, gets a thick inside edge which fortunately evades his stumps
down the pitch and clunked to long-on
firmly defended on the front foot
pitched up there and that's defended on the front foot
outside off and driven to cover
driven to cover for an easy single
clipped off the front foot in front of point
comes forward and looks to drive that through cover, but finds the fielder instead
right up there, and defended easily enough
oozed easily enough out to cover for a regulation run
strokes that one to mid-on and the strike's rotated once more
driven to mid-off this time
another quick single
yet another quick single, dinked up fine
strike stealing from Joyce
on the money and that pops up safe into the covers
turned off the thigh to square
dibbled into the covers and a run? "No!"
driven to mid-off
down leg, that's worked to the man on the 45 who doesn't gather it cleanly, but stops it nevertheless
driven to short midwicket
swept out to deep square leg

that dismissal was softer than a pack of extra-soft marshmallows: Bell going for the slog sweep and sending it high and straight down short third man's throat - not literally, as that would have been painful, but you get the idea
there he goes, down the track and sends an aerial drive over mid-off. There's an optimistic cry of "Catch it"
defended this time
outside off and that's driven easily to mid-on
half-shout for an lbw off a sweep, not close enough
defended forward
more defence - Joyce struggling to get Davison away still
pushes the batsman back on the back foot to defend
defended forward this time
defended on the back foot this time
Davison just loses his line and sends that down leg, Joyce sweeping down on top of it, shoulders high to low to please his coach
oh dear, another tame dismissal and a horrible shot - aiming to reverse sweep that, misses the ball completely the ball clips off stump
"Howzat?!" demands Dhaniram, drifting that in nicely. Well, it's not out, missing off
defended forward
pushed right up there and Collingwood defends
worked to square for a quick single
soft, softer, softest. Pietersen pops the ball back to the bowler, simple as that. A big blow for England, of course, not to mention the crowd.
worked that one to short midwicket
good running to come back for two, there
driven to cover this time
on middle and that's worked to midwicket
on leg and that's worked down to fine leg
driven to cover
worked off the front foot to midwicket
guided out to square for an easy single
driven to cover
chops that into the ground and Bagai snaps that with one hand
driven straight to mid-on
defended forward to end the over
drags that a touch short outside off and that's driven out to Cummins at long-on
leading edge pops into space on the on-side - half a chance of a catch - and then they scrambled through a risky single
short and the batsman waits for it, moving on to his backfoot to crash a cut shot to point
drops that short and with width, and the batsman delights in cutting it to point
defended forward
driven to mid-on and there's a chance of a run out
low full toss gets the treatment - a spanking in front of midwicket
driven to cover
tickled behind square
reverse sweep timed sweetly down
played down off the back foot , the pace taken off the ball
on the front foot and that's defended forward
tossed up outside off and that's sent aerially, but safely, through cover and it fair rockets away
worked off the back foot softly into midwicket
driven to long-on
drags it a touch short and that's driven to mid-on
swept away behind square
tossed up there, straight, and that's dinked to square
booted through the covers
driven to long-on and that's cannoned back in quickly
above waist height and the batsman gamely tries to get over the ball and work it to leg, but can't quite manage it
full and straight and that's driven forward
another attempted yorker and would have been close if Bopara had have missed: he didn't, and worked it in front of midwicket
a quick two straight and that's some good running from England
defended this time
pulls it flat and straight and without much power towards mid-on
driven forward to mid-on
worked off the back foot, slowly, into midwicket
drags that short and a single to long-on brings up the 200
short and that's eased out in front of midwicket this time for another quick single
driven into the on-side
outside off and that's driven out to extra cover for an easy single
timed straight to cover
driven out to quarter-past on the clock face from the batsman's perspective
gets away with a low full toss, just pulled to midwicket
flicked the wrists over that one to midwicket
up there and tickled away square
on leg, worked behind square
straight and that's dinked into the leg-side
well played to wide long-off, with some unurgent fielding
worked off the legs behind square
comes down the wicket and slashes that in front of midwicket
defended on the front foot this time
slog-sweep on one knee and that rockets away

oh dear, average. High full toss on the hips, bunted over midwicket and that crashes into the hoardings. The umpires are consulting - will they take him off here? He's already been warned once. Yes, Bhatti has been brought on to finish the over.
oh dear, very average. New bowler, similar result - short and that's swept on one knee over midwicket
driven to cover
outside off, rubbish fielding at cover and that had to be tidied on the boundary by Billcliff
a touch of spin deceives the batsman who was already through on his pull shot - and it goes through to the keeper
low full toss, great balance off the front foot, and that's wrested in front of midwicket, bisecting the fielders
right up there and that's driven out to long-on. There's a chanciness about the second run but in the end the batsman is well home at the non-striker's end AKA, in this instance, The Danger End
tickled out to midwicket
reverse sweep and the bowler makes a lone, throaty roar of a Howzat?
driven to midwicket and that's a fifty for Collingwood off just 41 balls
horrible shot, attempted reverse sweep, missed it totally and there goes his off stump - Bopara showing all of the sticks, there
driven to mid-on
comes forward and brutes that through cover but Bhatti did well to dive and stop that at full stretch
driven out to the boundary just inside the boundary
ooh, nearly got an outside edge on that one, Dalrymple slapping his bat into the ground there
oh dear - fishing at a very wide one with a premeditated sweep looking to paddle it fine, but made a late decision to try to dink it late to third man and sent it straight to the keeper instead
drops his bat on to that one and works it behind square for a quick single
high full toss on the off side, the bowler gets away with it, and that's worked into the covers
straying onto leg and that's worked off the toes behind square
reverse sweep, middled, and that's a good shot, rattling away behind square
comes down the track and that's a cheeky aerial drive over mid-off
on leg and there's a loud appeal from the bowler for lbw but down the wrong line
horrible attempt to sweep that, misses it, and that spins away, dying, from the lefthander
quicker delivery, reverse sweep along the floor behind square and that's another good shot from Nixon
Collingwood again goes square and there's a touch of a misfield inside the boundary, Cummins's arms going above his head in frustration
good running from Nixon to the danger end, having turned quickly and got home quite comfortably in the end
down on one knee and clatters that one away from off stump through the leg side
doesn't really middle it this time and that goes into the midwicket area - Nixon calls him back for the second, but he turns the offer down
poor line and Nixon flicks that over short fine-leg, really getting holding of that and pinging it, really
full toss and that's a good way for Nixon to end England's innings, with a straight six

inn2.comm: nice swing from Anderson and that's not a bad length first up, the batsman leaving the ball
rushed off the pads to fine leg
left alone outside off and that one flies through at waist height
done by pace and it's on to him faster than expected, but he got away with it with an aerial bunt that cleared mid-on
big appeal, but the umpire says 'Not out', as that hit him outside the line
swing again, good bowling from Anderson and that's eased into the leg side
that one hung in the air for a while as Barnett, his feet stuck in the ground, drove that aerially
right up there and a touch of inswing from Plunkett - a strangled appeal
bowled him neck and crop there, the batsman shouldering arms to one which nipped back in off the seam and that's a dreadful misjudgement
swing and a miss, Bagai's feet getting trapped in the crease there and he stands tall, prodding at air
arcs gently away this time and that's easily left alone outside the off stump
comes forward and pokes that one down to third slip
left alone outside off
ooh and he goes on the charge, hammering Anderson but straight to the man at mid-on
solidly blocked out on the back foot
oh but he plays and misses at that one. A gentle outswinger which he fished at and immediately admonished himself, throwing his head back in disgust
just outside off and it got big on him, as he punched it hard off the back foot - one-handed, too, the left hand slipping off the bat
driven on the up for four. Quite simply, just smacked it on the up in front of square, using the pace of the delivery to send it torpedoing for four
lovely away swing is too good for the right-hander who again fishes and misses
full this time from Plunkett, and an easier length for the batsman who drives, crisply, if without properly timing it, to mid-off. Well run, mind
straight and just short of a length, rising on the batsman who is turned around and defends it with the straightest of bats
gone! No. But very nearly. Full and straight, no swing there, and he drove on the up - appearing to get an outside edge but it was turned down by Peter Parker
handsomely driven through extra cover
another play and miss
oh, fabulous shot - real class in that shot, punching it through cover off the back foot
fuller - better from Anderson - but again it's handsomely driven, albeit straight to mid-off now
much better length - just short of "good" - but he's right behind it, defending it solidly on the front foot
fuller still, attacking the off stump, and it's firmly defended
short and uppercut to third man
wide and left alone
gone this time. Like Anderson's ball in the over before, it was short but too straight to be uppercutting and he picked out third man
wild and woolly down the leg side, Nixon scampers to his left to collect
expansively driven through extra cover - he gave that some humpty. Vaughan gives chase but he was only treading water
huge shout for lbw as Davison is rapped on the pads trying to flick a straight delivery through midwicket. It looks very, very close indeed...just not close enough
and he goes for the same shot, makes contact this time but finds midwicket
too full; too wide and Davison easily works it through the off side
too wide again from Anderson and rightly left alone
on off stump, better this time and it's blocked out
dreadful delivery; brilliant shot. A powerful, commanding square cut.
a cracking ball this time just leaving the right-hander who fishes and misses
blocked out on the back foot
pushed to mid-on
cut over backward point, though not fully in control of that stroke
magnificently driven but again he picks out the fielder, this time at mid-off
solidly defended on the front foot
a swing and a miss outside the off stump. That's the line
full, but a bit too wide. Solidly defended nevertheless
driven once more to mid-off
pushed out into the covers
poor stroke - trying to savage a cut through the covers but missing it by miles
defended out into the covers
and he goes for a huge drive but can't time it, and it bobbles out rather tamely into the covers
skips down the pitch and tries to swat it over midwicket, missing it completely
and again he comes down the pitch. Anderson sees him coming this time, sends it wider - so wide that Davison couldn't reach it; so wide that it was called a wide
superb shot, driving through the line and over Anderson head for four
magnificent shot! Absolutely hammered it over extra cover for four
whipped through midwicket
pushed to cover
poor bowling. Just too wide
that's the length for Plunkett, dragging him forward and he swishes and misses
down the wicket he comes and another swing-n-miss
driven on the up to mid-off
and Davison practically runs down the pitch this time, attempting to smack it over midwicket but he gets a bottom edge
gone this time. He absolutely middled it, almost too well, smacking it aerially and straight to Ian Bell at deep extra cover
good ball on off stump and it's watchfully defended
Anderson really bent his back there - much quicker delivery, kept out by the batsman on the back foot
blocked out off the back foot
far too short, but it turned quite prodigiously away from the right hander
fuller and straighter and defended
firmly pushed out into the covers
fuller and he gets it into the gap at cover this time
excellent ball on middle-and-off, turning away, but well defended
blocked out to end the over
too straight from Anderson and whipped around the corner for a couple
too wide this time, defended to gully
on middle-and-leg but the batsman can't break through midwicket
short of a length and he goes back to defend
wide of the off stump and left alone. He couldn't have reached it with a bargepole
excellent ball with which to end the over. On off stump, a little bit of movement and attacking the stumps. Firmly defended.
well bowled! Batsman came confidently forward to defend, the ball fizzing past his outside edge
touch shorter from Monty, played out into the covers
well bowled again, passing the outside edge. This is quick, from Monty, really sharp and flat
dabs down on this one on off stump
another huge appeal from Collingwood at first slip. Nothing from Nixon as the batsman is rapped on the pads
but he's gone for it this time! A simple swing through the arc sends the ball miles over long-off
left alone outside off - miles too wide
outside off and left alone
swing and a miss - good outswing there
ooh nearly! Nice banana swing and it falls just short of Joyce at first slip
flicked wristily over midwicket
firmly defended
again defended solidly but that's a fine first over from Bopara. Nice and tight
huge heave ho and is very nearly bowled
pushed out into the covers
quicker ball which is clumped into the off side
straighter and turned to leg
quicker still! 60mph, defended on the front foot by the smiling batsman
beautiful bowling. He held that back, dropped it short and another fish-and-miss by the batsman
outside the off stump and blocked out on the front foot
a big appeal from Bopara as the batsman is wrapped on the pads, but he's well outside the line
bit of outswing there, but it's too short and cut down to third man to Monty
quicker and fuller, but too straight - though the batsman rather missed out
oh lovely ball, a classic away swinger which he played and missed at
a jaffa! Just a touch shorter, cutting away from Billcliff's tentative forward defence and the off-stump was sent back
flicked to leg. Wrong line from the Montster
lovely ball on off stump, firmly defended by Mulla
drifting down the leg side, flicked through midwicket with ease
just a touch fuller this time which is clamped down upon
straighter and he comes forward to smother the spin
full and straight - blockhole-full in fact - and dug out
left alone outside off
swinging into the right hander this time, quicker too and the batsman gets into a middle, the ball hitting his midriff
straighter this time but he could only work meekly to leg
smacked on the up, square of the wicket. Only a fraction too short, but certainly too wide, and hammered for four
pushed out to point
defended out to cover
shoulders arms outside off to a sharply spinning delivery
tossed up, but too full and it's driven to mid-on
worked through midwicket
oh, lovely bowling, beating the outside edge
again a fine ball on off stump which was well defended on the front foot
and he sweeps, misses, the ball ballooning up onto the leg side
forced past point for a single, without really moving his feet or gaining much power into the shot
drifting down the leg side...and it's called a wide
bosh. Just a touch shorter, and wide enough to clump it square past point. Power.
full and straight, driven hard to mid-off
flat-batted to mid-off
on middle stump and it's neatly worked to mid-on's right
defended on the front foot
that's a stunning shot, the most effortless pick-up off his legs and he timed it absolutely perfectly. Immense class in that stroke, ending a poor over from Bopara
on off stump, swinging away and it's flicked to leg
too straight from Collingwood allowing a single down to fine leg
and a swing-and-a-miss
ah that's much better, swinging into the right hander this time - half a shout for leg-before as scamper a single to leg
calmly pushed out to cover
defended on off stump
on one knee and that's driven to cover where it's well fielded by Joyce diving over in it
outside off, turning back into the righthander who chops down on it to gully
tickled round fine, a mere caress
extra loop and turn there for Dalrymple, the batsman just leaning over the ball, missing it and it crashes into his pads
defended down
comes forward, looking to turn that to leg, but the ball crashes into his legs
just to say on leg and that's turned to midwicket
straight and whipped away to square
on the money and inched to short cover
pressed down into the covers
driven into the covers again
pressed forward again
wide and that trickles down leg, evading Nixon
tucked away off the legs
huge shot! Just opens his arms and lifts that over mid-off for four - only just short of the rope
good reply, and the batsman creeps over it to defend
tickled off the legs
down leg and that's worked down to deep backward square leg
left alone outside off
worked forward to mid-off
pokes at that and there's a thick edge away through third man for four
another steer to wide third man
on a good length and a hint of swing away and that's defended down
up there and defended down
on the money and defended forward
turns back into the righthander and defended just at the last minute
worked into midwicket
driven to cover
slowly driven to long-on
popped up safe into the midwicket region
overstepped, and that's defended into the cover region
pitches well outside off and late cut behind point
chopped down to fine third man
tidily defended
more tidy defence
plenty of movement in the air and off the seam there, but the batsman deals well with it in defence
driven out to the man at extra cover
drags it down a touch and that's worked down to third man
turn and that's a good shout
driven out to cover
a thick edge flies over the waiting vultures in the gully region
chipped in the air but into space
defended forward on the front foot
on leg and that's rushed out to midwicket
worked out off the backfoot behind point
nearly gets a fine edge on that one
nearly falls over in his rush to defend that one
outside off and that's worked down to wide third man
